x|x(x-1)+y(y-1) \rightarrow x|y(y-1)
y|x(x-1)+y(y-1) \rightarrow y|x(x-1)
x
x^2-x(1+y)+y^2-y=0
(1+y)^2-4(y^2-y)=1-3y^2+6y=4-3(y-1)^2
x, 4-3(y-1)^2\ge0\implies (y-1)^2\le\frac43\implies -\frac2{\sqrt3}\le y-1\le \frac2{\sqrt3}
\frac2{\sqrt3}<2, -2<y-1<2\iff-1<y<3
y
0\le y\le2
2|xy|\le x^2+y^2
|x|+|y|\ge \frac{1}{2}(x^2+y^2)
(x\pm 1)^2+(y\pm1)^2\le2
